    "Abdullah et al. [81] and Aziz et al.",
    "[82] confirmed that POFA enhances resistance to chloride, acid, and sulfate attacks, while also decreasing water permeability by up to 20%.",
    "BentoniteBentonite significantly improves concrete's resistance to acid attacks, reducing weight loss by 10-15% and water absorption by 5-10%, which lowers permeability and enhances protection against aggressive agents.",
    "Yang et al. [85] reported a 76.47% increase in impermeability and better pore structure, boosting resistance to chloride and sulfate penetration.At a 16% replacement level, bentonite also prevents bleeding and refines the microstructure, improving water resistance According to Mesboua et al.",
    "Akbar et al. [87] confirmed these findings, noting enhanced sulfate resistance and durability at a 20% replacement level."
